# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PrintNest API — REST Client Test File
# Requires: VS Code extension "REST Client" (ms-vscode.vscode-restclient)
#
# FULL FLOW (run steps in order):
#   1. Admin:  create store → register device
#   2. Public: create job → upload file → finalize → quote → pay → generate OTP
#   3. Device: use tools/simulate-device.sh (HMAC signing needed, see bottom)
#
# QUICK START:
#   1. docker-compose up
#   2. Set @adminKey below
#   3. Run steps 1a → 1b → 2 → 3 → 4 (see Step 4 note) → 5 → 6 → 7 → 8
#   4. Copy jobId and sharedSecret from responses into the @variables
#   5. Run tools/simulate-device.sh for the device side
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl  = http://localhost:5000

# ── Set these before running ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
@adminKey = replace_with_your_32_char_admin_key

# ── Copy from API responses after running steps below ────────────────────────
@storeId   = store_supermart_01
@deviceId  = dev_supermart_abc12345
@jobId     = paste-job-id-here
@objectKey = paste-object-key-here

###

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ADMIN: Stores
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Step 1a: Create a store
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/stores
Content-Type: application/json
X-Admin-Key: {{adminKey}}

{
  "storeId": "{{storeId}}",
  "name": "SuperMart Hitech City",
  "address": "Hitech City, Hyderabad, Telangana 500081",
  "latitude": 17.4486,
  "longitude": 78.3908
}

###

### Step 1b: List all stores (verify creation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/stores
X-Admin-Key: {{adminKey}}

###

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ADMIN: Devices
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Step 2: Register a device
# ⚠ IMPORTANT: Copy sharedSecret from the response immediately — it is NEVER shown again.
# Paste it into simulate-device.sh when testing the device flow.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/devices
Content-Type: application/json
X-Admin-Key: {{adminKey}}

{
  "deviceId": "{{deviceId}}",
  "storeId": "{{storeId}}"
}

###

### List all devices (verify registration)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/devices
X-Admin-Key: {{adminKey}}

###

### Deactivate a device (blocks it from auth)
# PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/devices/{{deviceId}}/deactivate
# X-Admin-Key: {{adminKey}}

###

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PUBLIC: Job Lifecycle
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Step 3: Create a print job
# Response contains: jobId, uploadUrl (presigned MinIO PUT), objectKey
# Copy jobId and objectKey into @jobId and @objectKey above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Step 4: Upload file to MinIO
# The uploadUrl from Step 3 is a presigned PUT URL pointing directly to MinIO.
# Replace the URL below with the uploadUrl from the Step 3 response.
# You can use any small PDF file — or create one:
#   printf '%%PDF-1.4\n1 0 obj<</Type/Catalog/Pages 2 0 R>>endobj\n2 0 obj<</Type/Pages/Kids[3 0 R]/Count 1>>endobj\n3 0 obj<</Type/Page/MediaBox[0 0 612 792]/Parent 2 0 R>>endobj\nxref\n0 4\n0000000000 65535 f\n0000000009 00000 n\n0000000052 00000 n\n0000000101 00000 n\ntrailer<</Size 4/Root 1 0 R>>\nstartxref\n153\n%%%%EOF' > /tmp/test.pdf
#
# PUT <paste-presigned-upload-url-here>
# Content-Type: application/pdf
#
# < /tmp/test.pdf

###

### Step 5: Finalize upload (confirms file is in MinIO, transitions Draft → Uploaded)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs/{{jobId}}/finalize
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "objectKey": "{{objectKey}}"
}

###

### Step 6: Get a price quote (sets options, transitions Uploaded → Quoted)
# color must be "BW" — "Color" is coming soon (disabled)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs/{{jobId}}/quote
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "copies": 1,
  "color": "BW"
}

###

### Step 7: Mock payment (transitions Quoted → Paid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs/{{jobId}}/pay-mock
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Step 8: Generate OTP (returns 6-digit code — show this to user)
# Can be called multiple times — each call invalidates the previous OTP.
# OTP expires in 6 hours.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs/{{jobId}}/otp/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### Regenerate OTP (if user wants a fresh code)
# Same endpoint — calling it again generates a new OTP and invalidates the old one.
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs/{{jobId}}/otp/generate
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {}

###

### Check job status at any point
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/printjobs/{{jobId}}

###

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PUBLIC: Store Map
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Get all active stores (used by customer map view — no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/public/stores

###

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DEVICE FLOW — Use tools/simulate-device.sh
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Device endpoints require HMAC-SHA256 signing which cannot be computed inline
# in a .http file. Use the device simulator script:
#
#   bash tools/simulate-device.sh <DEVICE_ID> <SHARED_SECRET_BASE64> <OTP_CODE>
#
# Example (after Steps 1–8 above):
#   bash tools/simulate-device.sh dev_supermart_abc12345 "base64secret==" 482917
#
# The simulator runs the full device flow:
#   POST /api/v1/device/heartbeat          ← verifies device auth works
#   POST /api/v1/device/release            ← OTP → file token
#   GET  /api/v1/device/printjobs/{id}/file ← download PDF to /tmp/
#   POST /api/v1/device/printjobs/{id}/printing-started
#   POST /api/v1/device/printjobs/{id}/completed
#
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

###

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SYSTEM
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###
